Monday, September 14th, and Tuesday, September 15th, students in grades 3-10 will be taking a practice math and reading benchmark test. These tests are to gauge their knowledge on their current year material and understanding.

Please encourage your child to do their best on these tests and not get overwhelmed. While we do not expect anyone to understand all the material presented in the tests, we do expect students to work hard.

With the knowledge gained from these tests we will be able to better direct their learning in the classroom.

For the 20-21 school year, car rider pickup and drop off will remain the same. Students will be dropped off at the cafeteria. Please only drop students off at the cafeteria and not before 7:30 am.

Once students are dropped off, they will go though the side door and have their temperature taken. They can then get their breakfast and head to first period class.

The only exception to this will be our pre-k and k classes. Their teachers will meet them in the cafeteria where they will eat breakfast and then be escorted to their classroom.

This link will explain this process with the school map and directions

https://youtu.be/teJjazk164k

If you have any questions please call the school.

post_text:
As the start of the 20-21 school year approaches, JISD will roll out all the new changes for the school year.

Up first is our school hours. We have extended our school hours from 8:00-3:45. Adding in this extra time allowed us to extend our passing periods giving students more time between classes.

We also ask that no student be dropped off before 7:30 each morning. In the past we could make arrangements for early drop off, but this year our teachers and staff already have enough extra duties to attend.

If you have any questions regarding school hours please call the school.

Congratulation to two of our Jonesboro FFA members!

Trey Harbour was named the State Star in Production winner this morning during our virtual state convention. He advances to National FFA competition and is awarded a $1000 scholarship.

Bracy Foote obtained her State Lonestar Degree. This is the highest honor at the state level that an FFA member can receive.

Congratulations to both of our FFA members for their hard work and dedication.

Jonesboro Buyers Club is raising funds for the 2021 Youth Fair. They are raffling off 10 head of brangus heifers. If you win they can deliver the animals to your place or send you the check from sale barn.

Last year the Buyers Club was able to spend over $16,000 on Jonesboro students. They have a goal to double that for this years fair.

If you want a ticket contact Kendra Gustin, Mike-BethAnne Gann, Susan Millsap Smith, Than Foote, Joe Foote, or Cody McFarlin.

You can Venmo the funds (@kendra-Gustin) or PayPal (gannbam@outlook.com). Make sure you send the name and phone number you want on the ticket.

Jonesboro FFA members, parents and guests:
For the first time in the history of the FFA our State FFA Convention is being held virtually. Please click the link below to sign in and watch our wonderful organization’s convention. Please be sure to tune in at 10am on Friday 7/10 for the results of the Star Awards (Trey Harbour has advanced to the final 4 in the state and interviews for secure his placing this Tuesday 7/7) and Bracy Foote will be awarded her State FFA Degree also on Friday at 10 AM.
I hope you enjoy what you will see. It is the biggest highlight of our summer and we are so sad that we are not face to face, but we are very grateful to our association that has
worked tirelessly to bring it home to us.
https://convention.texasffa.org

post_text:
Varsity Cheer Tryouts

Any current or new student wanting to join the already existing JISD Varsity cheer squad this is for you. Due to some unforeseen circumstances we will be hosting another cheerleading tryout. Due to restrictions this will be video based. I will list criteria below. I along with two judges will review video submissions. The number of those who make it will be decided once the number of submissions are complete. Please email kaylasellers@jonesboroisd.net for information on where to submit videos.

Tryout Criteria

Must perform:
- Cheer of choice- Please show as much spirit as possible during cheer.
- Fight song dance or dance at least one minute in length
- Must show a toe touch and one other jump of choice
- Must show tumbling of choice

Submissions will be taken from 6/16/20-6/30/20. Again this is a virtual tryout only for those who wish to join the current cheer squad. No current cheerleader will trying again. Thanks!

Dallas Isom....thank you. Thank you for all of your years of dedication to JISD. You have been invaluable to this school and community. I do know that you turned in your retirement letter after the last day teachers are on campus so we could not throw you a party. You would leave campus without a fuss because that's how you are.

Please know that you will be missed dearly. Thank you for teaching our kids and loving them like your own. JISD is better for you having been here.

Today we celebrated an amazing lady, friend and teacher. Cynthia Cate has spent the last 50 years dedicating her life to the education of children. She has been with Jonesboro ISD through good and bad times. Her expertise, love for children, friendship and smile will be missed dearly.

Mrs. Cate, thank you. Thank you for loving our children like your own. You can never be replaced on campus or in our hearts. We pray your retirement brings you many years of joy.

shared_text:
Gatesville Recreation Department
May 20 at 12:42 PM ·

As of May 20, 2020, the Gatesville Recreation Department has decided on a new athletics schedule for the remainder of the year. We had to make tough decisions during this time to ensure the health and safety of our entire community and the surrounding areas. We believe that our new schedule is the best course of action at this time.

We will have a youth baseball/softball season for kids that registered for the pre t-ball, t-ball, 8U, and 10U divisions. This season will run from September 5- October 10. There will be safety guidelines that will have to be followed to ensure the safety of everyone. There will be more to come on these guidelines once the season gets closer.

For those of you that had kids registered for the 12U, 14U, and 15U divisions, we are canceling those divisions at the time. Refunds will be sent out within the next few weeks. The remainder of the 2020 soccer season is also being canceled at this time.

Thank you for your patience and support during this difficult time. If you have any questions, feel free to contact Seth at seth.phillips@ci.gatesville.tx.us

post_text:
Govoner Abbott and other state officials just announced new guidelines for graduation ceremonies. JISD is working on finalizing plans for our graduation. The ceremony will look different and we have many safety requirements to work out.

As of this moment graduation is scheduled for May 22nd at the football field. The time, ceremony format, and number of guests allowed will be decided very soon. Once again, please be patient with us as we think it all through.

We are still filming graduation this Thursday as a backup. While we have the all clear to host graduation at this time, we want to make sure we are still prepared if that order changes.

We are extremely thankful to be be able to plan a graduation for our seniors. To end the year with a little bit of normalcy will warm our hearts.

From Chisholm Craftworx:

We're taking submissions from Jonesboro seniors to win a 2-4 t-shirt pillow. You provide your favorite T-shirts you no longer wear or want to preserve as a memory (2-4) and we turn them into a pillow for you!
To enter the contest you just have to submit your favorite high school memory, it doesn't have to be a school memory, just one from your high school years. You can place your submission at Chisholmcraftworx@gmail.com please put "contest" in the subject.
We will pick ONE winner on May 15th.

post_text:
Pre-K and Kindergarten registration packets will be ready Monday, April 27th. You must pick the packets up from school.

For pre-k, once you have a complete packet your name will go on the list. We will put transfer students on a waiting list until June 1st. This will give us time to get all in district students enrolled first. Once that date passes, we will use the names off of our transfer list to fill up the class. We will go in order that we received complete packets.

If your child is already in pre-k for the district you do not have to fill out a new packet for kindergarten.

Please call the school if you have any questions.

post_text:
Today, Texas Governor Greg Abbott amended his Executive Order, calling for all schools in the state of Texas to close for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. This means JISD will remain closed to the public.

JISD will continue to provide distance learning to all of our students through May 22, 2020. JISD will also continue to serve breakfast and lunches each weekday through this situation.

Please look for an announcement late next week concerning prom and graduation. We expect to receive information and guidance from Mike Morath, Texas Commissioner of Education, next week regarding graduation ceremonies.

Miss you all,
Kendra Gustin
Principal JISD

To ensure everyone can keep track with assignments during our time learning at home, I wanted to point out a new feature on Parent Portal. You can now see grades that do not have grades inputted in the grade book. You will NOT receive grade alerts for blank grades. This will help you keep up with assignments at home a little better.

All you have to do is click show all assignments. The screen shots below are from my phone screen. It will look differently on a computer screen but the language is the same.

Please let me know if you need any help.

Common symptoms of #COVID19 are fever, dry cough, & shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor & #StayHome. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor & seek care immediately.

Spanish
Los síntomas comunes de #COVID19 son fiebre, tos seca y dificultad para respirar.Si tiene síntomas leves, llame a su médico y quedate en casa.Si desarrolla síntomas graves, como dificultad para respirar o presión en el pecho, busque atención médica de inmediato. #StayHome

God Bless you all and stay safe!

Thank you all!

post_text:
Students and parents:

Teachers and staff are already preparing lessons for next week. Due to the fact that this week was our spring break, we have not had a chance to meet as a faculty to collect lessons and prepare materials. We are meeting throughout the day Monday. Please expect lessons to start coming through Monday afternoon and Tuesday.

We will have digital options as well as print copies. A schedule of times to pick up print copies and locations will be posted. Teachers will also support lessons with videos and other means of communication.

I just wanted to update everyone on a time line of materials and work as this is new to us all.

If at any time you have questions please call the school. We ask that you call to keep the number of visitors to the campus to a minimum. We are all answering emails and texts as well.

Know that we already miss our students. We love hearing their spring break adventures and our hearts ache not being able to see them. Give the kids big hugs from their teachers and tell them we love them!

post_text:
🍋Lemon Face Challenge🍋

Principal Kendra Gustin was challenged to do the lemon face challenge so she got grades pk-3rd to help her. Many of the kids on campus love Layla and pray for her daily. Her light and testimony through this difficult time is beyond inspiring!

Jonesboro ISD challenges the surrounding school districts!

Help us raise money in honor of Layla Evetts💜

Here are instructions:
The goal is to raise money and awareness for DIPG everywhere! The rules are simple: 1. Explain the goal of the challenge, 2. Nominate folks you want to do it too, 3. Suck on a lemon and give us your best face, 4. Post to social media. #5 is optional, but would be super cool: DONATE!!! we are asking that in lieu of gifts, everyone donate to The Cure Starts Now in Laylas honor.

https://thecurestartsnow.salsalabs.org/lemon-face-challenge-layla-evetts/index.html

#loveforlayla
#lemonfacechallenge

post_text:
We are a little behind on our posts and pictures from stock shows. We’ve been to Ft Worth, San Angelo, and currently in San Antonio.
Trey Harbour won Southdown Breed Champion in FW. Bracy, Pate, and Truett Foote placed with their lambs that they raised, and Kenny Warrick placed 8th with his lamb.
Bracy Foote won Reserve Champion Dorper Ewe at San Angelo and also showed a market wether. Kenny Warrick showed two market wethers. Kennah Piller placed 9th with her goat and showed a market wether.
Kase Laster showed his gilt last week in San Antonio at the breeding show and Kenny Warrick showed a ewe at the breeding show.
Today, Trey Harbour placed 2nd with his Southdown wether and Kenny Warrick showed a market wether. Dalton Kennedy shows tomorrow and we will be back late Friday for the market pig show.
We will update with pictures after this weekend!

post_text:
Cheer Tryout Information

Tryout lists for High School and Junior High have been placed in the hallway by the glass door to the front office. Students may sign up there. This year along with judges scores will be teacher/school evaluations that take into consideration grades, attendance and behavior. Parent meeting and Try-Out dates will be listed below. Please make sure if you are interested in trying out that you plan on being at the meeting with a parent to go over rules/expectations, costs and new information regarding next year. Practice days for tryouts will be given following the parent meeting. Dates can be subject to change if basketball is in the playoffs.

Dates:
Parent Meeting- January 20 @ 6PM Cafeteria

Try-Outs- February 28 with High School starting first @4:15

post_text:
Sports Picture Notice

Boys Varisty, JV, and Junior High basketball photos will be taken tomorrow during the boys sports period. Normally prior notice would be give but given when football ended we did not have time to do so. Picture forms are going home with the varsity & JV boys today and JH will be given them tomorrow. Junior High girls basketball photos will be this Wednesday.

Please make sure to turn in order forms by Friday so I can place an order and get them to you by next week!

If you have previously ordered photos for football or girls varsity basketball the first round order has been done and they will be here this week.

Thanks for your support of our kids and the yearbook!

Don’t forget to order that too! You can do so online or through me at the school!

Kayla Sellers

post_text:
https://www.latimes.com/sports/highschool/story/2019-12-27/6-man-football

Jonesboro was a feature in the LA Times on an article regarding 6-man football. To our past, present and further players, your legacy for the sport has shined all the way to California. Keep up the hard work and know that we are very proud of each of you.

As the last line in article says we “leave together,” I’m reminded of just how blessed our Jonesboro family is to have each other. Enjoy the rest of your Christmas break!
